A chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Eze Chukwuemeka Eze, has advised two chieftains of the party in Rivers State and former federal lawmakers, Senator Magnus Ngei Abe and Hon. Igo Aguma, to join the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Eze, in statement made available to LEADERSHIP in Port Harcourt, commended former Rivers State Commissioner for Education, Chief Alwell Onyesoh, for dumping the APC for the PDP. The APC chieftain alleged that Onyesoh’s departure from the party only added credence to his previous warnings that Abe and his supporters have an agenda to decimate the APC in the state and pave way for the PDP before they formally decamp for their individual and collective rewards. He said: “While I commend Chief Alwell Onyesoh, for his bold step, I appeal to Senator Abe and Igo Aguma, to toe the path of honour by officially joining Onyesoh in PDP, which is their place of harvest. “They should allow peace take its place within the Rivers APC. Their continued stay is a bad omen for the party.” Eze, who is former national publicity secretary of the defunct new Peoples Democratic Party (nPDP), alleged that Governor Nyesom Ezenwo Wike, is lobbying to join the APC, as the PDP family is in shambles. He said: “I commend Chief Onyesoh for the path he has chosen, but I worry a bit and sympathize with him, owing to the fact that the family he joined is in shambles, as Governor Wike is currently lobbying to secure a place in the All Progressives Congress.”